notesStmt.note: Condition: Some pages adhered (f. [42-43], [50-51], [59-60], [115-116]) and therefore not photographed for the digital facsimile; damp staining sometimes obscuring text at the bottom of the page.

msContents.summary: A Hanafi treatise on Islamic inheritance law.

author.persName: Anqirāwī, Shujāʻ ibn Nūr Allāh, active 16th century

support.watermark: Countermark of trefoil and initials EB.

supportDesc.extent: 169 leaves : 95 x 190 mm, bound to 98 x 190 mm

collation.p: Paper, 169. Catchwords on each leaf, lower left verso.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black and red ink; pointed.

decoDesc.decoNote: Illuminated headpiece surmounted polychrome and gold arches. Some rubrications; textblock border-ruled in gold or red.

binding.p: Red leather binding with marbled paper.

origin.p: Copy completed in Rajab 1092 A.H. (1681 CE) by Aḥmad ibn Muṣṭafá (colophon).

keywords.term: Inheritance and succession (Islamic law)--Early works to 1800
